               <head>Laṭāʾif al-akhbār by Rashīd Khān</head>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85001521 http://id.loc.gov/authorities/sh85064913">
                  <summary>
                     <title>Laṭāʾif al-akhbār</title>, called <title>Tārīkh-i
                                Qandahār</title> in the colophon, a detailed account of <persName role="subject" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164656959.0x000001 viaf_27879596">Dārā Shukūh</persName>’s
                            unsuccessful siege of <name type="place" key="subject_n83042981">Qandahār</name> in 1063/1653 by Rashīd Khān known as Muḥammad
                            Badīʻ, also called Rashīd Khān Badīʿ al-Zamān or Badīʿ al-Zamān
                            Mahābatkhānī. 
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_609-item1">
                     <author key="person_f3492">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Rashīd Khān </persName>
